### **1.2 Design Principles**\
\
#### **Safety First**\
- **Never recommend harmful actions**\
- **Check contraindications before every recommendation**\
- **Provide alternatives when primary action is contraindicated**\
- **Include warnings and cautions prominently**\
\
#### **Evidence-Based**\
- **Every recommendation linked to clinical guideline**\
- **Evidence level documented (A, B, C)**\
- **Source attribution (SSC 2021, ACC/AHA, NICE, etc.)**\
- **Uncertainty acknowledged when evidence is weak**\
\
#### **Actionable**\
- **Specific, not vague** ("Administer Piperacillin-Tazobactam 4.5g IV" not "Give antibiotics")\
- **Time-bound** ("Within 1 hour" not "Soon")\
- **Measurable outcomes** ("Target MAP \uc0\u8805 65 mmHg")\
- **Clear escalation paths** ("If no response, notify ICU")\
\
#### **Context-Aware**\
- **Patient demographics** (age, weight, pregnancy, renal function)\
- **Medication history** (allergies, current meds, prior responses)\
- **Clinical context** (location, time of day, available resources)\
- **Institutional protocols** (hospital-specific pathways)\
\
#### **Clinically Validated**\
- **Physician-in-the-loop design** (recommendations, not orders)\
- **Override capability** with documentation requirement\
- **Feedback loop** for continuous improvement\
- **Regular clinical review** of recommendation quality\
