\
### **2.3 Protocol Matcher**\
\
**Purpose:** Identify which clinical protocols apply to current patient state\
\
**Matching Algorithm:**\
\
**Step 1: Trigger Detection**\
```\
For each protocol in knowledge base:\
    Evaluate trigger criteria against patient state\
    If all criteria met:\
        Add protocol to matched_protocols list\
        Calculate confidence score (0-1)\
```\
\
**Example Triggers:**\
\
**Sepsis Protocol:**\
- SIRS criteria \uc0\u8805 2 AND\
- Suspected infection (fever OR leukocytosis) AND\
- Elevated lactate >2.0 OR\
- Organ dysfunction markers\
\
**STEMI Protocol:**\
- Chest pain AND\
- ST elevation on ECG AND\
- Elevated troponin\
\
**Hypoglycemia Protocol:**\
- Glucose <70 mg/dL AND\
- Symptoms (confusion, sweating, tremor) OR\
- Glucose <54 mg/dL (severe)\
\
**Step 2: Priority Ranking**\
```\
Rank matched protocols by:\
    1. Urgency (life-threatening first)\
    2. Confidence score\
    3. Time sensitivity\
    4. Complexity (simpler protocols preferred if equivalent)\
```\
\
**Step 3: Conflict Resolution**\
```\
If multiple protocols conflict:\
    - Prefer life-threatening condition\
    - Consider temporal sequence (sepsis before hypoglycemia)\
    - Flag for clinician review if ambiguous\
```\
\
---\
\
### **2.4 Action Builder**\
\
**Purpose:** Generate specific, actionable recommendations from protocols\
\
**Action Types:**\
\
#### **1. DIAGNOSTIC Actions**\
- Lab orders (STAT, urgent, routine)\
- Imaging orders (X-ray, CT, ultrasound)\
- Procedures (ECG, ABG, cultures)\
- Consultations (ID, cardiology, critical care)\
\
**Example:**\
```\
Action \{\
    type: "DIAGNOSTIC",\
    priority: 1,\
    title: "Obtain Blood Cultures (2 sets)",\
    description: "Draw before antibiotic administration",\
    timeframe: "STAT - before antibiotics",\
    specific_instructions: [\
        "Use sterile technique",\
        "2 sets from different sites",\
        "Minimum 10mL per bottle",\
        "Label with time and site"\
    ],\
    rationale: "Identify causative organism for targeted therapy",\
    evidence: "SSC 2021 - Grade 1B recommendation"\
\}\
```\
\
#### **2. THERAPEUTIC Actions**\
- Medication administration\
- Fluid resuscitation\
- Oxygen therapy\
- Procedures (intubation, central line)\
\
**Example:**\
```\
Action \{\
    type: "THERAPEUTIC",\
    priority: 1,\
    title: "Administer Broad-Spectrum Antibiotics",\
    timeframe: "Within 1 hour",\
    primary_recommendation: \{\
        medication: "Piperacillin-Tazobactam",\
        dose: "4.5g IV",\
        route: "Intravenous",\
        frequency: "Every 6 hours",\
        duration: "To be determined by culture results"\
    \},\
    alternatives: [\
        \{\
            medication: "Ceftriaxone 2g + Vancomycin 15-20mg/kg",\
            indication: "If MRSA suspected"\
        \},\
        \{\
            medication: "Meropenem 1g",\
            indication: "If multi-drug resistant organism risk"\
        \}\
    ],\
    contraindications: [\
        "Penicillin allergy (use alternative)",\
        "Severe renal impairment (adjust dose)"\
    ],\
    monitoring: [\
        "Renal function",\
        "Allergic reaction (first 15 minutes)",\
        "Clinical response (24-48 hours)"\
    ]\
\}\
```\
\
#### **3. MONITORING Actions**\
- Vital sign frequency\
- Lab recheck intervals\
- Symptom assessment\
- Response evaluation\
\
**Example:**\
```\
Action \{\
    type: "MONITORING",\
    priority: 3,\
    title: "Enhanced Vital Signs Monitoring",\
    frequency: "Every 15 minutes \'d7 2 hours, then every 30 minutes",\
    parameters: [\
        "Blood pressure",\
        "Heart rate",\
        "Respiratory rate",\
        "Oxygen saturation",\
        "Temperature",\
        "Mental status"\
    ],\
    goals: [\
        "MAP \uc0\u8805 65 mmHg",\
        "SpO2 \uc0\u8805 94%",\
        "Lactate clearance \uc0\u8805 10%"\
    ],\
    escalation_criteria: [\
        "MAP <65 despite fluids \uc0\u8594  consider vasopressors",\
        "SpO2 <90% \uc0\u8594  increase oxygen, consider intubation",\
        "Worsening mental status \uc0\u8594  urgent reassessment"\
    ]\
\}\
```\
\
#### **4. ESCALATION Actions**\
- Physician notification\
- Rapid response team activation\
- ICU transfer\
- Specialty consultation\
\
**Example:**\
```\
Action \{\
    type: "ESCALATION",\
    priority: 1,\
    title: "Activate Rapid Response Team",\
    timeframe: "IMMEDIATE - within 5 minutes",\
    contacts: [\
        \{role: "Intensivist", extension: "2222"\},\
        \{role: "RRT Nurse", pager: "5555"\},\
        \{role: "Attending Physician", notify: true\}\
    ],\
    brief: "Septic shock, NEWS2 8, lactate 2.8",\
    preparation: [\
        "Ensure IV access (large-bore)",\
        "Have emergency medications ready",\
        "Prepare for possible ICU transfer"\
    ]\
\}\
```\
\
#### **5. MEDICATION_REVIEW Actions**\
- Medication adjustments\
- Drug discontinuation\
- Drug interactions\
- Adherence assessment\
\
**Example:**\
```\
Action \{\
    type: "MEDICATION_REVIEW",\
    priority: 3,\
    title: "Hold Telmisartan During Acute Phase",\
    rationale: "ARB may worsen hypotension in sepsis",\
    recommendation: "Hold until hemodynamically stable",\
    restart_criteria: [\
        "Off vasopressors \'d7 24 hours",\
        "MAP stable >65 mmHg",\
        "Volume resuscitation complete"\
    ],\
    alternative: "Monitor BP closely, may need adjustment"\
\}\
```\
