### **3.3 Knowledge Base Loading & Management**\
\
**Storage Options:**\
\
#### **Option 1: File-Based (YAML/JSON)**\
**Pros:** Easy version control, human-readable, CI/CD integration\
**Cons:** Slower loading, requires parsing\
\
#### **Option 2: Embedded Database (H2/SQLite)**\
**Pros:** Fast queries, relational structure\
**Cons:** Harder to version, less portable\
\
#### **Option 3: Distributed Cache (Redis/Hazelcast)**\
**Pros:** Very fast, shared across Flink instances\
**Cons:** Requires external service, cache invalidation complexity\
\
#### **Recommended: Hybrid Approach**\
- **Protocols & Guidelines:** YAML files (version controlled)\
- **Medication Database:** Embedded H2 database (loaded on startup)\
- **Runtime Cache:** Hazelcast for frequently accessed data\
\
**Loading Strategy:**\
```\
STARTUP SEQUENCE:\
\
1. Load static knowledge from files\
   - Parse YAML protocols\
   - Load medication database\
   - Build index structures\
\
2. Validate knowledge base\
   - Check protocol completeness\
   - Verify medication references\
   - Test rule logic\
\
3. Cache in distributed memory\
   - Store in Hazelcast\
   - Enable hot reload\
\
4. Ready to process events\
```\
