## \uc0\u9889  **10. Performance Optimizations**\
\
### **10.1 Caching Strategy**\
\
```\
// Cache frequently accessed knowledge base elements\
CACHE LAYERS:\
\
Layer 1: In-Memory (JVM Heap)\
    - Active protocols (most frequently used)\
    - Common medication information\
    - Evidence references\
    Size: 100 MB per task manager\
    TTL: 1 hour\
    \
Layer 2: Distributed Cache (Hazelcast)\
    - Full medication database\
    - All protocols\
    - Guidelines\
    Size: 1 GB cluster-wide\
    TTL: 24 hours\
    Refresh: On knowledge base update\
    \
Layer 3: File System (RocksDB)\
    - Patient history state\
    - Recommendation history\
    Size: Unlimited (disk-based)\
    Persistence: Checkpointed\
```\
\
---\
\
### **10.2 Parallel Processing**\
\
```\
// Parallelize independent operations\
PARALLEL BLOCKS:\
\
1. Protocol Matching (can evaluate protocols independently)\
    protocols.parallelStream()\
        .map(p => evaluateProtocol(p, patientContext))\
        .collect()\
\
2. Contraindication Checking (per action)\
    actions.parallelStream()\
        .map(a => checkContraindications(a, patientContext))\
        .collect()\
\
3. Evidence Fetching (independent lookups)\
    actions.parallelStream()\
        .map(a => attachEvidence(a))\
        .collect()\
```\
\
---\
\
### **10.3 Early Termination**\
\
```\
// Stop processing if high-confidence match found early\
FUNCTION matchProtocolsWithEarlyExit(patientContext):\
    \
    FOR EACH protocol IN protocols_sorted_by_priority:\
        \
        match_result = evaluateProtocol(protocol, patientContext)\
        \
        IF match_result.confidence > 0.9 AND\
           match_result.is_definitive:\
            // Very high confidence, definitive match\
            // Don't need to check other protocols\
            RETURN [match_result]\
    \
    // Continue full evaluation if no early match\
    RETURN evaluateAllProtocols(patientContext)\
```\
