## \uc0\u55357 \u56960  **16. Deployment Strategy**\
\
### **16.1 Phased Rollout Plan**\
\
```\
DEPLOYMENT PHASES:\
\
Phase 1: Shadow Mode (Month 1)\
    - System generates recommendations\
    - Recommendations NOT shown to clinicians\
    - Log all recommendations\
    - Compare with actual clinical actions\
    - Measure: Agreement rate, false positives, false negatives\
\
Phase 2: Passive Display (Month 2)\
    - Recommendations shown in dashboard\
    - Non-interruptive display\
    - No alerts/notifications\
    - Clinicians can view but not required\
    - Measure: View rate, feedback, usefulness scores\
\
Phase 3: Active Alerts - Low Acuity (Month 3)\
    - Show recommendations for P3-P4 (Medium/Low priority)\
    - Allow clinicians to get familiar\
    - Limited alert fatigue risk\
    - Measure: Acknowledgment rate, action rate, time-to-action\
\
Phase 4: Active Alerts - High Acuity (Month 4)\
    - Add P1-P2 (Urgent/High priority)\
    - Still no P0 (Critical)\
    - Monitor closely for adverse events\
    - Measure: Clinical outcomes, override rate, satisfaction\
\
Phase 5: Full Production (Month 5+)\
    - Enable all priority levels including P0\
    - Full interruptive alerts for critical\
    - Continuous monitoring\
    - Measure: Full outcome metrics\
\
Rollback Criteria:\
    \uc0\u10007  Harmful recommendation detected\
    \uc0\u10007  Agreement rate <70%\
    \uc0\u10007  Override rate >60%\
    \uc0\u10007  Physician satisfaction <3/5\
    \uc0\u10007  System performance degradation\
    \uc0\u10007  Clinical outcomes worse than baseline\
```\
\
