## \uc0\u55356 \u57281  **19. Summary: Module 3 at a Glance**\
\
### **What It Does**\
- Receives enriched patient data from Module 2\
- Matches clinical situations to evidence-based protocols\
- Generates specific, actionable, time-bound recommendations\
- Checks contraindications and provides alternatives\
- Prioritizes actions by urgency and clinical impact\
- Provides rationale and evidence for each recommendation\
- Tracks recommendation history and prevents duplicates\
\
### **Key Features**\
- **Protocol-Driven**: Evidence-based clinical guidelines\
- **Context-Aware**: Patient demographics, allergies, medications, chronic conditions\
- **Safety-First**: Contraindication checking, alternative generation\
- **Actionable**: Specific orders, not vague suggestions\
- **Evidence-Based**: Every recommendation cited with evidence level\
- **Smart Deduplication**: No alert fatigue from repeated recommendations\
- **Priority-Ranked**: P0 (Critical) to P4 (Low) with scoring\
\
### **Clinical Value**\
- Reduces time to critical interventions (sepsis antibiotics, etc.)\
- Improves protocol adherence (bundle compliance >85%)\
- Prevents medication errors (contraindication checking)\
- Reduces cognitive load (prioritized, consolidated recommendations)\
- Supports clinical decision-making without replacing physician judgment\
\
### **Technical Highlights**\
- Real-time processing (<5 second latency)\
- Scalable (1000+ concurrent patients)\
- Configurable (YAML-based knowledge base)\
- Maintainable (external configuration, no code changes for guidelines)\
- Observable (comprehensive metrics and monitoring)\
